Problem Statement

1)Ragu is fascinated by number manipulation and wants to create a program that reverses a given integer. He has a keen interest in understanding how numbers can be reversed.

Write a program to help him achieve this task.

Input format :
The input consists of an integer num, representing the number to be reversed.

Output format :
The first line of output prints an integer representing the reversed digits of the input number.

Refer to the sample output for formatting specifications.

Code constraints :
103 ≤ num ≤ 109

Sample test cases :
Input 1 :
12458
Output 1 :
85421
Input 2 :
28463
Output 2 :
36482

SOLUTION:
import java.util.Scanner;
class main
{
    public static void main(String[] args)
    {
        Scanner scan=new Scanner(System.in);
        int a=scan.nextInt();
        int d;
        int r=0;
        while(a!=0)
        {
            d=a%10;
            r=r*10+d;
            a=a/10;
        }
        System.out.print(r);
    }
}
